title: Sussan Ley Defends Liberal Party As Mark Speakman Resigns As NSW Opposition Leader | 10 News+
description: Sussan Ley has defended the Liberal Party’s track record on net zero, immigration, and defence policy. She insists her party is united and that criticism of her shift towards the political right is only coming from the Canberra bubble. It comes as more turmoil continues within the Liberals, with Mark Speakman handing in his shock resignation as New South Wales’ Opposition Leader. title: Former Olympic Snowboarder Turned Alleged Drug Lord On FBI’s Most Wanted List | 10 News+
description: Ryan Wedding, a former Olympic snowboarder from Canada, has been added to the FBI’s 10 most wanted list. Authorities are offering up to US$15 million for information leading to his arrest. Wedding is accused of running a transnational drug trafficking operation, and the charges are connected to his alleged involvement in the killing of a witness who was about to testify in a US federal court. description: Beloved Matildas superstar Mary Fowler has made a bombshell claim in her new book ‘Bloom: Creating A Life I Love’, alleging she faced racism when playing for the French club Montpellier HSC. title: Australian Music Industry Concerned Over Rise Of AI-Generated Songs | 10 News+
description: Australian musicians are concerned over a global surge in AI-produced tracks. At this year’s Golden Guitars, judges suspected four tracks to be completely AI-generated, and issued a blanket ban on the technology. Industry experts hope the fight against artificial intelligence will be led by committed artists and their fans, who want to create and listen to real music. title: US Continues Peace Deal Talks With Ukraine And Russia | 10 News
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy welcomed US Secretary of the Army, Daniel Driscoll to Ukraine's capital of Kyiv.  In a meeting between the two, Driscoll described Ukraine's fight against the Russian invasion as "remarkable".  Driscoll was accompanied by several other high-ranking US Army officials to assist in peace talks in Ukraine.  In Washington D.C., White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt told reporters that US Secretary of State Marco Rubio and Special Envoy Steve Witkoff were deep in discussion with both Ukraine and Russia over a potential peace deal. title: COP30 Climate Summit Evacuated After Fire Disrupts Negotiations In Brazil | 10 News
description: Talks at the COP30 climate summit in Brazil were disrupted on Thursday after a fire broke out in the venue, triggering a mass evacuation.  Flames and smoke were seen raging from one of the country exhibition pavilions before hundreds of attendees were rushed outside where fire engines raced past.  The UN has said the fire had been brought under control and 13 people were treated on site for smoke inhalation. It is not yet known what caused the blaze.  It’s understood the talks were in the final hours of trying to agree on next steps to tackle climate issues, but the fire has halted negotiations. title: Trump & JD Vance Snubbed For Former US Vice President Dick Cheney’s Funeral | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump and Vice President JD Vance have been left without an invite to the funeral service for former Vice President Dick Cheney.  Former US leaders, lawmakers and other dignitaries gathered at Washington's National Cathedral to remember Cheney, who was a vocal opponent of Trump.  Cheney's daughter, former Representative Liz Cheney, remembered him as one who "knew the bonds of party must always yield to the single bond that we share as Americans.”  Former President George W. Bush gave a eulogy honouring him, and Former President Joe Biden also attended the service. title: How Olympian Ryan Wedding Landed On The FBI's Most Wanted List | 10 News
description: An Olympic snowboarder has scored another medal, landing himself on the podium of the FBI's Most Wanted list.
